// Dev secrets override — Debug builds only.
//
// INSTRUCTIONS:
// 1. Copy this file to Secrets-Dev.xcconfig (same directory).
// 2. Fill in the DEV Supabase project's values (project: doom-ctrl-dev).
// 3. NEVER commit Secrets-Dev.xcconfig — it is gitignored.
//
// This file is optionally included by Secrets-Debug.xcconfig AFTER
// Secrets.xcconfig, so these values override the production ones for Debug
// builds. Release builds never include it and always use production.
//
// Why: without this, Debug and Release both resolved to the same Supabase
// project, so local/dev testing wrote into production data. The SUPABASE_URL
// below points Debug at a separate dev project instead.
//
// The anon key is a PUBLIC client key (it ships in the app binary), so this is
// not a high-value secret — it is gitignored only to keep the two environments'
// keys from being mixed up in version control.

SUPABASE_URL = https:/$()/YOUR_DEV_REF.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = your_dev_anon_key_here
